
WorldManager::CheckMusic

Starts/stops the combat music, playing the combat music if any of
the following are present:
* A hostile, non-destroyed enemy ship
* A hostile environment
* Intruders
* Mind-controlled crew


SoundControl::StartPlaylist

When switching playlists (eg from changing sectors), fade the current music
out over 750ms, and two seconds after the fade starts, start the new
playlist's first track.


SoundControl::StartCombat and ::StopCombat

These fade (across two seconds) between the current track's combat and explore
versions. It seems both of them are tied together, so the explore version
will continue playing muted while in combat (thus the times match up exactly).

The explore track is only played at 80% of the volume of the combat track.


SoundControl::SwitchTracks

This switches to the next song in the playlist, going through linearly and
repeating once it reaches the end.

This is called by OnLoop whenever the current song ends.
